egr221a.interfaces.worklists

Class PriorityWorkList<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • egr221a.interfaces.worklists.WorkList<E>
      • egr221a.interfaces.worklists.PriorityWorkList<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of elements in the worklist; must be comparable
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<E>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    MinFourHeap

    public abstract class PriorityWorkList<E>
extends WorkList<E>
    A subclass of WorkList that stores its elements in priority order. All subclasses of this class implicitly agree to the contract to be a priority queue. The "priority" of an element should be determined via compareTo(). The direction (min or max) is up to the implementation.
    Version:
    SP 2017
    Author:
    Mikyung Han
